  "text": "As mentioned in the introduction, common heuristics do not have a finite approximation ratio for GCBP [CITATION_1] , and other heuristics have a higher approximation ratio than one would expect. Another difference is that sorting items in a non-decreasing order of their sizes is better than a non-increasing order.",
